---
layout: default
title: "Build inspection from CAD"
description: "Software-first defect detection for high-mix manufacturing. CAD goes in, inspection logic comes out — no rules to rewrite every time the part changes."
permalink: /
---

<!-- Hero -->
<div class="py-16 sm:py-24">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 lg:px-8">
    <p class="eyebrow text-primary-600 mb-6">Rose City Robotics</p>
    <h1 class="text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-8xl">
      <span class="block">Build inspection</span>
      <span class="block">from CAD</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-8 text-xl leading-8 text-gray-900 max-w-2xl">Software-first defect detection for high-mix manufacturing. CAD goes in, inspection logic comes out — no rules to rewrite every time the part changes.</p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-gray-600 max-w-2xl">Built by Joseph Cole, PhD. Deployed on practical edge hardware for pass/fail and defect location that plugs into real QA workflows.</p>
    <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-x-6 gap-y-3 items-center">
      <a href="mailto:hello@rosecityrobotics.com?subject=Feasibility%20Sprint" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Start a Feasibility Sprint</a>
      <a href="/why-it-works/" class="text-sm font-semibold leading-6 text-gray-900">See how it works <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
      <a href="/articles/" class="text-sm font-semibold leading-6 text-gray-900">Read the research <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Today vs With RCR -->
<section class="bg-gray-50 py-20">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
    <div class="border-t-2 border-gray-300 pt-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-500">Today</h2>
      <p class="mt-1 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900">Rules break on every revision.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-gray-600">Rules-based vision systems require manual programming for each part, each finish, each tolerance. When the design changes — and it always does — you're back to rewriting rules. High-mix lines can't keep up. Your inspection station becomes a maintenance burden, not a quality signal.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="border-t-2 border-primary-600 pt-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-primary-600">With RCR</h2>
      <p class="mt-1 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900">CAD goes in. Logic comes out.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-gray-600">RoseVision CAD Studio trains directly from your STEP files. No rules to maintain. No large labeled dataset to collect first. When the part changes, rerun from CAD. Pass/fail and defect location that stays current with your design and deploys on the edge hardware your floor already runs.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

